nd misrepresenting his true achievement. Recasting Freud as an inspired humanist and reconceiving psychoanalysis as a form of moral inquiry, Alfred Tauber argues that Freudianism still offers a rich approach to self-inquiry, one that reaffirms the enduring task of philosophy and many of the abiding ethical values of Western civilization.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 0aPsychoanalysis and philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044250240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978140083692540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400836925423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400836925.jpg  a978-3-11-044250-2  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK